citeinfo.title: 2010 US Census Block Groups in Florida (with Selected Fields from 2010 Redistricting Summary File and Summary File 1)

descript.abstract: This dataset contains the US Census Bureau 2010 Census Block Groups for the State of Florida with selected fields from the 2010 Redistricting Summary File and Summary File 1. Some of the fields included in this dataset are total population, age of the population, population by race, density and percentage of population by race, and household occupancy. This data is at the block group level. In addition, fields have been added and calculated. This data is designed for use within the Florida Department of Transportations Efficient Transportation Decision Making Process (ETDM). However, the subset of redistricting fields included herein is useful for a variety of applications and uses. If you are looking for census block group data with complete attribute data in its original form from the Census Bureau, please see the FGDL layer CENBLKGRP2010_SF_AUG11.
descript.purpose: For the research and analysis of the 2010 Census Redistricting Summary File and Summary File 1 at the Census Block Group geography level. The data contains selected fields from the 2010 Census. Census Block Groups are geographic entities made up of Census Blocks and that are contained within the same Census Tract. Block Groups generally contain between 600 and 3,000 people, with an optimum size of 1,500 people.

procstep.procdesc:
The Redistricting Summary File was downloaded from the Census in .pl format from http://www2.census.gov/census_2010/01-Redistricting_File--PL_94-171/Florida/ and the database was compiled using the process steps in http://www.census.gov/rdo/pdf/0HowToUseMicrosoftAccessShells.pdf
The 2010 TIGER line files were downloaded from the following site: http://www.census.gov/geo/www/tiger/tgrshp2010/tgrshp2010.html When received the data was in Geographic Lat/Long projection. The data was projected to Albers HPGN.
The data was then joined to the 2010 Tiger/MAF shapefile based on the GEOID10 field. Selected fields (see below) were renamed to be similar to naming from 2000 FGDL census data fields and duplicate fields were deleted. The following fields were extracted from the tables and renamed: P0010001 - TOTAL POPULATION P0010003 - WHITE ALONE P0010004 - BLACK P0010005 - AMERICAN INDIAN P0010006 - ASIAN P0010007 - NATIVE HAWAIIAN P0010008 - SOME OTHER RACE P0010009 - 2 OR MORE RACES P0020002 - HISPANIC OR LATINO P0020003 - NOT HISPANIC OR LATINO P0030001 - TOTAL POPULATION 18 YEARS AND OVER H0010001 - TOTAL HOUSING UNITS H0010002 - OCCUPIED H0010003 - VACANT

Summary File 1 was downloaded from the US Census Bureau from http://www2.census.gov/census_2010/04-Summary_File_1/Florida/fl2010.sf1.zip and the database was compiled using the process steps in http://www2.census.gov/census_2010/04-Summary_File_1/0HowToUseMSAccessWithSummaryFile1.pdf
